        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 4 at 2:44PM CDT until August 4 at 3:30PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>SVRCRP

The National Weather Service in Corpus Christi has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Nueces County in south central Texas...
Eastern Jim Wells County in south central Texas...

* Until 330 PM CDT.

* At 243 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Banquete, or
near Driscoll, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Robstown, Driscoll, Banquete, Agua Dulce, Petronila, and North San
Pedro.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 672 and 680.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
